The paper deals with a coding scheme for non-adaptive group testing, which involves identifying a small number of defective items from a large set. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS), as well as distributed computing (cs.DC) and machine learning (cs.LG) since the proposed scheme involves iterative decoding. Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the scheme in the presence of noise, which is a topic in signal processing (cs.SI).
